org.sbml.jsbml

Interface Quantity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CallableSBase, Cloneable, NamedSBase, NamedSBaseWithDerivedUnit, SBase, SBaseWithDerivedUnit, Serializable, TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Variable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Compartment, LocalParameter, Parameter, QuantityWithUnit, Species, SpeciesReference, Symbol

    public interface Quantity
extends CallableSBase
    A quantity is an element that represents a value with an associated unit that can be addressed through the identifier or name attribute of this element. Both the value and the unit may be directly declared by the quantity or may have to be derived.

    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        double getValue()
        Returns the value of this Quantity. In Compartments the value is its size, in Species the value defines its initial amount or concentration, and in Parameters and LocalParameters this returns the value attribute from SBML.
        Returns:
        the value

      • isSetValue

        boolean isSetValue()
        Returns true if the value of this Quantity is set.
        Returns:
        true if the value of this Quantity is set.

      • setValue

        void setValue(double value)
        Sets the value of this Quantity. Note that the meaning of the value can be different in all derived classes. In Compartments the value defines its size. In Species the value describes either the initial amount or the initial concentration. Only the class Parameter and LocalParameter really define a value attribute with this name.
        Parameters:
        value - the value to set

      • unsetValue

        void unsetValue()
        Unsets the value of this Quantity.
